China had 648 million short videos users as of June 2019, accounting for 75.8 percent of its netizen population, according to a report on China's Internet development released Friday. In the first six months of the year, 639 million people, or 74.7 percent of Chinese netizens, watched full-length videos such as TV dramas, variety shows and films online, said the report issued by the China Internet Network Information Center. A total of 759 million Chinese netizens have watched videos, including both short and full-length ones, in the first half of 2019, an increase of over 33.91 million from the end of 2018, the report said. 
